TY  - JOUR
T1  - Trying to Look Bad at Work: Methods and Motives for Managing Poor Impressions in Organizations
AU  - Becker, Thomas E.
AU  - Martin, Scott L.
Y1  - 1995/02/01
PY  - 1995
DA  - 1995/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256732
DO  - 10.5465/256732
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 174
EP  - 199
VL  - 38
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Intentionally looking bad at work is a type of impression management in which employees purposefully attempt to convey unfavorable impressions. Drawing on the employment experiences of 162 individuals, we documented five forms of such behavior: decreasing performance, not working to potential, withdrawal, displaying a bad attitude, and broadcasting limitations. Motives for managing poor impressions were also documented. The management of poor impressions was discriminable from the management of favorable impressions and self-handicapping. We provide a preliminary framework for understanding the management of poor impressions.
AB  - Intentionally looking bad at work is a type of impression management in which employees purposefully attempt to convey unfavorable impressions. Drawing on the employment experiences of 162 individuals, we documented five forms of such behavior: decreasing performance, not working to potential, withdrawal, displaying a bad attitude, and broadcasting limitations. Motives for managing poor impressions were also documented. The management of poor impressions was discriminable from the management of favorable impressions and self-handicapping. We provide a preliminary framework for understanding the management of poor impressions.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256732
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256732
Y2  - 2026/04/24
