TY  - JOUR
T1  - Studies of Individualism-Collectivism: Effects on Cooperation in Groups
AU  - Wagner, John A
Y1  - 1995/02/01
PY  - 1995
DA  - 1995/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256731
DO  - 10.5465/256731
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 152
EP  - 173
VL  - 38
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Data from 492 college students indicated that group size and individuals' identifiability, sense of shared responsibility, and levels of individualism or collectivism influenced peer-rated cooperation in classroom groups. Levels of individualism or collectivism moderated the effects of size and identifiability on cooperation but not those of shared responsibility. These findings suggest that models of free riding and social loafing provide insights into individualistic cooperation in groups but are limited in their ability to explain the cooperation of collectivists.
AB  - Data from 492 college students indicated that group size and individuals' identifiability, sense of shared responsibility, and levels of individualism or collectivism influenced peer-rated cooperation in classroom groups. Levels of individualism or collectivism moderated the effects of size and identifiability on cooperation but not those of shared responsibility. These findings suggest that models of free riding and social loafing provide insights into individualistic cooperation in groups but are limited in their ability to explain the cooperation of collectivists.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256731
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256731
Y2  - 2026/04/24
